caption: Stopped in on an recommendation by a friend. I had the balsamic and bleu pork belly sandwich and my honey had the french dip. We both agreed they were the best sandwiches we had enjoyed in a long time. The pot belly is so flavorful and tender. Buns were yummy too. We both had the lemonade which was very tasty. Stop in here, you won’t be disappointed!

We ordered the Havarti turkey sandwich and the 5th strew chicken. Both sandwich’s were warm and amazing. The homemade bread used on the sandwiches melted in your mouth. Both sandwiches were amazing. I highly recommend. Not a lot of seating inside but it’s worth it.

Yeah, it gets lines, but they have managed super well, with the procedures for cleanliness and service during these tough times. I'd swear by the Pork Belly BLT and the Crack Chicken, and don't forget to pick up some Mac n Cheese. They really are doing something special in downtown Springfield. Thanks!
The food lived up to the hype

Emily, Corey, Tyler, and staff make this place easily one of the best places to grab a bite.  Consistently delicious.  The amount of energy and attention these folks put into their craft is inspirational.  Long live Long 9!
Good food and friendly people!

Just ordered the Filipino Pork bowl and it was friggin amazing. Warm, creamy and just a tad spicy Tom Lincoln kha, served with crispy and juicy pork belly and a side of colorful and tangy Asian slaw. Served with a side of freshly made bread that was totally unnecessary but so delish it was like dessert! Super easy to drive up or walk up and grab takeout, with precise pick up times available when you order online. Treat yourself to some gourmet fare from Long 9!
Great Cuban and service was amazing! Will be back for sure!
The melon salad with pork belly was amazing! The potato skins were way too salty unfortunately.  But the service was great. Would definitely try it again.

I am amazed by the variety, creativity and deliciousness of Long Nine Junction's food.   They are consistent in providing high quality menu and warm hospitality in their service.  For me, this is the best restaurant in Springfield, Illinois!
All around GREAT! Long Nine junction sets the standard for outstanding pop and mom local grub! A kiss of bliss in each and every bite! Don’t miss out!

This place is really good. The sandwiches are great. The chicken with the Diablo sauce is really good. The Mac and cheese is good & creamy. Lots of good options & changing specials. The bread is homemade and really good. They also have some good desserts too.
Our favorite place to eat in Springfield! It has the best homemade food and friendly staff around.
Good food, clean restaurant, friendly staff. A delightful dining experience in a casual atmosphere.
If you are in Springfield you MUST  come here!  This place is amazing.  My favorite is the Balsamic N Blue sandwich.  Soooooo good!
Great food with a nice ambiance, we ordered chicken, roast beef and pork and it was all delicious!
Awesome lunch place

My partner and I just spent 36 hours in Springfield, and Long Nine Junction had the best food we tried in town. BUT the French Dip was probably the best I’ve ever had. The bun was soft and a little sweet, and the jus was lightly spiced and a little thickened- almost like a gravy, but not. I chose the side salad; it was dressed lightly and perfectly with a slightly sweet dressing that was probably balsamic vinegar with a little honey. Friendly, attentive staff and located very conveniently to the old state building and Lincoln’s law office.
Just a wonderful place. Great food. Great vibe from the staff and owners. You guys are working hard and doing great things.
Every item on the menu is incredible. House made bread and slow roasted meats. There's always a line for a reason - it's that good and more than worth the wait!
Damn this place is the only place you want to go for lunch.  You won't leave hungry.

This is a a small place and as a result, you may have to wait a bit for your food. However it's not worth the wait. My wife had the Cuba with Mac and cheese and I had a Memphis pulled pork sandwich with vegetable beef soup. All were incredibly good. Love goes into making this food for sure. Definitely worth a visit.

Hands down the best sandwich I've ever had, let alone a Cubano. The mac&cheese side was not far behind. Also very filling, especially for the price. Definitely coming back here on my next business trip.
Incredible sandwiches in a cozy atmosphere. Wish I lived closer I’d eat here often.
The atmosphere is amazing, the food is delicious and the staff are super friendly. Oh and there's an great selection of craft sodas and root beer.
Food was delicious
Long Nine Junction is beyond good. Some of the best food I’ve had anywhere, let alone Springfield. Do yourself a favor and check them out! Won’t be disappointed.
Got the meat and potatoes. Really good. It's a small restaurant, so seating is a hassle. But the food is worth it
Great food and service.
Outstanding! Havarti Turkey with carmelized onions was toasted to perfectly and Spicy Buttermilk Potato Soup was the perfect side.

How does this restaurant not have a Michelin Star?! Just moved here from Texas and had the best pulled pork sandwich I've ever had. The service was outstanding and the prices were more than reasonable.

I do not know how this restaurant doesn't have a perfect rating on Google. Everything I have ever eaten here has been PHENOMENAL and the service is great. This is one of the absolute must-do restaurants in Springfield.
Ate here 3 separate times during my stay in Springfield because the food and the people are just that amazing

This is an excellent place for a quick lunch.  Everything I've tried there is fresh, delicious food, with a number of fun, quirky options. I highly recommend their "mashies" (mashed potatoes) they're VERY good and housemade.  Perhaps the only disadvantage is that there's not a ton of seating in the old downtown building they use. The prices may seem a bit high at first for a locally owned Midwestern restaurant, but the price/quantity is quite reasonable, and you're paying for quality as well.   I highly recommend stopping by over lunch break, while grabbing a bite to eat between Lincoln sites, or whenever you want.
Great food served with a nostalgic twist all in a cozy, little place
This is my favorite place to eat in Springfield. Consistently rotating menu with intriguing daily specials. Services always top notch and food is always incredible.
Food good service was good. Prices are a bit high.

The food, service, and atmosphere were so amazing. I was so happy to come here and would definitely go back. The people are so friendly and the pulled pork and lemonade here is the best I have ever had.
O.M.G.  such delicious food and small craft root beer.  Excellent.
Cool atmosphere!! Great food!!
I honestly don’t know if I’ve ever had a better turkey sandwich with tomato bisque! My taste buds are still celebrating!
Great French Dip, baked potato, Mac & cheese & Black Cherry soda goes along with very accommodating staff & cool atmosphere!!

This place is terrific! While staying in Springfield for a few days we went with Google reviews and tried Long Nine Junction. If you are a fan of really good inventive, fresh food, well prepared, you need to eat at Long Nine.  First impression on walking in made us pause-it ain't fancy. But after looking at selections on the menu wall, we had to order. Delicious slow cooked pulled pork with a peach bbq sauce over creamy mac cheese. Heavenly. Cuban panini with house made fresh pickles. Yummy. The little green salad on each plate was dressed with something something so good I wanted more.  The housemade bread is wonderful, with a slight sweetness and tastiness that is a perfect compliment to the homey but elevated fare.  The staff was friendly, accommodating, and professional.  Good people who know what they're doing in the front of the house and the back.  If I lived in Springfield I'd eat at Long Nine often.
Great, wholesome food!
Very very good
Oh my GOODNESS! The food was absolutely amazing. Waitrer was polite and professional.  Will be going back again if I can.
Awesome sandwiches, great service.
It was great food and atmosphere. Went for lunch at 12 it was busy and everyone got their food in a very timely manner. Open face pot roast beef was excellent.
Bets spot downtown for lunch
I can't sing the praises of this place enough. Fantastic food made with love, staff that are genuine, helpful and kind, and great atmosphere. I can't wait to come back!

Lots of variety offered in sandwiches, salads, and stews. The breads for the sandwiches are super filling and delicious. I had a grilled cheese and my husband had the cubano for lunch and we were stuffed for the whole day. We will definitely come back to try everything else.
Great Chipotle steak sandwich, was warned it was spicy but there wasn't a hint of spice

I am from Peoria, Illinois and whenever I am traveling near Springfield I must stop here for lunch! Their food it taste so amazing and fresh. But I think what impresses me the most, is the friendly  I am from Peoria, Illinois and when ever I am traveling near Springfield I must stop here for lunch! Their food it taste so amazing and fresh. But I think what impresses me the most, is the friend staff. Every time I have come here, the place is packed! But that doesn’t stop each and every employee from giving you their best selves
Cuban was good
Very delicious, unique quick lunch spot.

Order at counter, get to know your seat neighbor, type of place.  French Dip was delicious.  They really must spend some time preparing their meat, not your average beef.  Watermelon lemonade.  YUM.   I think they also must have homemade bread because that too was amazing.   So to sum up...perhaps not for a business meeting, but a fun, good atmosphere, and savory lunch stop.
Amazing food, kind staff, fun atmosphere.
Quaint, nice atmosphere, delicious food. You might even run into the Governor while there. :)
Food was delicious, service was excellent. Everyone was so friendly. I would eat here again if I'm in the area.

Whatever your reason for being in Springfield, be it tourism, business, or existing in the town you live, you’d be remiss to neglect adding a visit to Long Nine to your list. They offer the best there is to be had for lunch downtown. Seating is limited, but definitely worth the wait, if you get there at a busy time.
Thoroughly enjoyed every time I have gone here. Burrito special is a must. Always something different and creative.
Nice spot across from the Old State Capital. Unique sandwich & side choices, everything I had was pretty tasty and high quality. Not a bad price either.
Look at these photos, they tasted as good as they looked.  This restaurant is a gem in Springfield!
Good sandwiches. Variety of chips are excellent. A wide variety of different soda drinks. Would definitely recommend.
Piss poor job on updating your website to let people know you're closed on Aug 3rd who traveled 3 hours to come eat at your restaurant. Thanks for the frustration. Won't be wasting our time again.
Delicious, fresh, and inventive sandwiches and salads.  Lovely staff, good music, and cozy environs.  Big thumbs up!!!
This is by far the best lunch place in Springfield!
Mojo pork: transcendent

The flavors of this place are amazing and definitely out of place for a small Midwestern town like Springfield. Specializing in "lunch time sandwiches" you'll find an amazing menu created from a chef who went to Le Cordon Bleu in Chicago and man does it show. The Tom Kha soup is a must get along with any of their pork shoulder sandwichs. I can't wait to come back and try more!
Best lunch! Fresh ingredients,  great service.

On a road trip headed back to KCMO and decided to swing through Springfield to grab a bite. Looked for a place that was a bit more unique on the map and stumbled upon this gem. We were definitely not disappointed. Super fast, super friendly and super good. Definitely recommend the place and if I go through Springfield again in the future I'll be sure to bring all my friends next time.
I’m always impressed with my meal and the rotating specials make a great addition. Clean, quick, and courteous! I highly recommend you try this place out.
The French dip sandwich is amazing! Well done Long Nine Junction. So good!!
Best place in town.

Friendly atmosphere, excellent food. My hubby had the French dip...hands down amazing. I had a caprese salad...amazing. LNJ come to Joliet by the new courthouse!! Please!!! We have zero good rest in Joliet!

I visited because of great reviews in the office. However, I found the experience lackluster at best. I ordered the French dip which I thought was impossible to do wrong only to be unpleasantly surprised. This was the blandest French dip I have ever been served in my life, devoid of flavor, salt and on par with boiled chicken. The only compliment I can give on the food is the ingredients are high quality, the execution besides looking good is completely lack luster.the bread is fresh baked and delicious.  They have a whole hipster aesthetic going on, serving food on metal trays and drinks in Mason jars (yawn, when is this trend going to end, it is so overdone and common feeling), yet they are lazy about it and tone deaf to efforts to support Illinois businesses. They are serving Boylan BottlingNew Jersey bottled soda in the state capital of Illinois, when Excel Bottling is about 1.5 hours away in Southern Illinois. Even in Missouri they serve Excel, supporting local companies (they forced me to  compliment Missouri, which is another low for the day).  I cannot see any justification for going here at lunch unless it is winter and you are desperate for a hot sandwich within walking distance. Even still you can get a toasted sandwich at Head West and and cold sandwich at Jimmy John's long standing Illinois companies that at least have flavor to their food.  Also the staff while not rude are not friendly at all.  TLDR; paid $10 for French dip with zero seasoning.
Excellent food, quick and friendly service.
First time here today. Was phenomenal. I had the Local BLT and mac and cheese. Can’t wait to go back. Everyone was super friendly too.
It was ok , clean place, wish they had a better drink selection. It was cold and i wanted a coffee or hot chocolate they didnt have neither.

Had to share a pic before I hammered it all. Half of the brisket sandwich, plenty of meat with cheddar sauce & a little horseradish - comes with a side as well.  If you’re in Springfield or visiting you have to eat here or you’re doing yourself a disservice.
Small counter style restraint with awesome food! These people know how to cook.you will find an interesting menu with unique blends of flavors. Very reasonably priced.
Ridiculously good food.
This place is super unique. Their food is super fresh, tasty, and healthy. There are no friers so I felt okay with what I was eating. The bread is AMAZING!
I had the Balsamic and Blue.  Hands down the best sandwich I've ever had.  The different flavors oozing from this masterpiece was amazing.
The food and service here are always top notch. Inventive, tasty meals and many improvements on classics that make them even more satisfying

Amazing lunch spot. It's rare that straight chicken is a standout, but here it is. The adobo bowl is one of the best dishes I've devoured in a while. And if those two are this good, I'm certain that the rest are too. Do not pass Long Nine up!

This place is amazing! Not only was the owner and staff very friendly and explained what all was in different meals, every item in all three meals that we ordered was fantastic. They make all the food from scratch even down to the pickles. We will definitely be back!
First time eating here  and definitely won't be the last time either. I got the Slow Roast Beef and wow was it amazing. Tender, thickly sliced peices and the aujus was slightly thick like a gravy.
Lunch was awesome as always!!! Very friendly atmosphere!! The works are always always nice!!! Highly recommend eating there!!!
Love the food
Incredible!!!!
I’m in Springfield a couple times a month for work from Chicago and this is he highlight of my trip. Fantastic every time, I’m only bummed they’re a 3 hour trip from where I live.
Cool vibe and great food. The garlic bread grilled cheese sandwich is the best grilled cheese I’ve ever had. I will definitely make a return visit in the future.

Pulled pork, French dip, and Monterey chicken were spectacular! The staff were all very friendly and helpful, and the prices were reasonable considering the quality and quantity of food. We would come back in a heartbeat!

Stopped here for lunch and glad we did. The menu had plenty to choose from. I had the French dip with a cup of clam chowder which was wonderful. The staff was great and asked several times if our food was okay and even thanked us when we left. The place is small and the seating is like community seating which was something I was not use to but we met some very nice people at our table. Overall I would eat here again when In the area I highly recommend eating here.
Great food and atmosphere!
Really good. Wonderful bread.

Great little place with good food. We were a little confused about how things worked when we got there. You order at the front, then get you drinks and find a seat. They call out your number when things are ready and bring it over to you.

This is THE BEST lunch spot in Springfield. The food is fresh and homemade and the flavor combinations are unique and delicious. I make this place a priority to eat at when visiting family in Springfield. I have tried 5-6 different menu options and I am always blown away by how consistently delicious all of the food is. The staff are always friendly and attentive. There needs to be more places like this in Springfield!

Omg the food here is awesome fresh homemade every day. The menu changes monthly except for a few main items, You tastebuds wont be disappointed You are paying for fresh quality food FYI the pork belly is mouthwatering delicious and tender, enjoy

The decor is factory themed and enjoyable. The food is on the more expensive side of affordable. Think $20 per person. However, the food is not worth the cost. If they reduced their prices, their rating would improve.

Loved this little place with a great view. We were visiting for the day and some friends recommended Long NiNe Junction for its convenient location and amazing food. It did not disappoint and would definitely go back if I visit again.  Also, quick shout out to their sandwich bread and friendly staff!
Amazing food
Quick, friendly and DELICIOUS
Excellent sandwiches! Quick place to grab a delicious lunch! Currently open 11-3. Friendly service!
Great salad.

I experienced a horrific event while dining.  A lightweight young lady who was sitting on the end of a bench, fell to the floor when the bench flipped on her.  My husband was walking by when it happened a was hit by the bench on his wrist while it was coming up.  This caused severe pain, swelling and bruising to his hand, much less the distress felt by the young lady on the floor.  There are no stable chairs within the premises, only benches which are precarious at best.  The available seating is not suitable for a full grown mature adult or senior citizen.  After consulting with the owner about what happened, she was flippant and argumentative and was rather proud of their seating design, and had no intentions of modifying anything.  I would not recommend trying to sit in the premises; however, the food was flavorful, albeit overpriced.

I just went here for the first time. I had a BBQ turkey sandwich and my wife had the cubano. Both were very good.  I look forward to eating here again. There were lots of good looking things on the menu.  The inside is pretty small but at 12:30 for lunch we got our food pretty quickly and there were a few seats to pick from.
The best sandwich I've had in years!!! Full of meat and seasoned perfectly!!! Seating was a hassle,but worth it!!!

We wanted to try something new and so glad we did! Perfect little yummy place! The staff was very friendly! It is a small location and not a lot of seating but it worked for us. The food was delicious! We had grilled cheese, downtown club, pork belly, Mac n cheese and mashies(mashed potatoes). Very good!!! We will be back!
Wonderful flavors, friendly service, imaginative combos - loved it!
Delicious!!!
The hype is real, food was amazing
Amazing food!! Great service!! Clean and very nice atmosphere! ♥️♥️♥️♥️ Definitely going back soon!
Great food! Come early as their tables do tend to get full fast.
Amazing food. Favorite place to eat downtown.
Balsamic and Blue, you will not be disappointed.

This place was great for a quick and tasty meal. There are a ton of 5 star reviews so I decided to try it out for lunch. I ordered the balsamic and blue sandwich with a cup of tomato bisque soup.  Food promptly came out of the kitchen and was served hot and fresh. The only complaint I could even find was that some parts of my pork belly were harder to chew but for the most part it was tender and delicious. The soup was fantastic as well.  I recommend this for a quick bite to eat but it can get cramped inside. If you're looking for a quick lunch and are in the area this has got to be one of the best places to go.
Neat little hipster kitsch retro establishment. Fresh buns on display. Kitschy mason jars and tin containers not the best choice for dipping sauces.
Some of the best food in town. Wish they were open longer though
Great sandwiches
Great food with beautiful and cozy atmosphere.
Absolutely scrumptious. Everything I have ever had here is tasty and flavorful. They really have a special touch with meat, such as pot roast and  pulled pork. My daughter loves their mac and cheese.
Amazing! Wife works down town and has been trying to get me to try this place for a while. Let's just say I've definitely been missing out!
The seevice was good and the food was fantastic.
Unique menu. Tastes great and good service
Stop there every chance I get....Every thing is delicious.
Great homey made food. I had 5th street Turkey and apple pie homemade ice cream. Both of excellent quality and flavors. Also the staff is kind and welcoming.

This place owns so hard. Me and a pal were passing through town and wanted the best local place food we could find online. A quick search led us to Long 9 Junction and the reviews seemed too good to be true. The hype was real. Our sandwiches were served on house-baked sweet rolls which was a genius idea. What was inside the rolls cannot be properly put into words. Check this place out if you're anywhere near Springfield, IL.
Cozy and really good food.
Awesome place, good food and great vibe. Owners check on you while you eat. Very cool!!!!
Amazing and soulfully pleasant !

I had the best stew here, my first trip, and I was enamored with the rolls.  The stew had large pieces of multiple vegetables which were magnificent. Fantastic comfort food and a lovely little place to eat.  I can't wait to go back!
Great sandwiches. They are only open for lunch. Definitely would go back if we are in Springfield.

This is an awesome sandwich place! They bake their buttery sandwich bread freshly every day. My order of pork belly sandwich was perfect, and the portion of the meat is quite generous! It was right across from the Old State Capitol, and a short walk from Lincoln Home, so definitely check this out and enjoy when you're in town.
This is a perfect place for food. Service is great, food is awesome. Its not costly.
I had one of the best sandwiches of my life here!
Good food,but.......no fried foods.     I really wanted burger and fries.  Service was great!
I wish Springfield had more places like this. Great food and atmosphere, right downtown, so it’s easily walkable.
Some buddies and myself stopped in here! The food, the atmosphere, and the staff are all top notch! One of the best places to eat in Springfield by far!! 5 stars is not enough!
Amazing food, great service and close to a historic spot! 100% recommend! The French dip is a favorite of mine!
Very good food.  Pleasant atmosphere.

Been there several times, and the food is usually awesome. However, they can sometimes run their dishes on the salty side. I had a citrus chicken meal that was very salty and lacked much of the citrus element. Be aware it has first come first serve communal seating. I enjoy it, but it's not for everyone.

I ate there for the first time last Tuesday, August 21st. So good I went back the next day and took the wifey. I have tried the French Dip sandwich which was very good. I have also tried the Santa Fe bowl which was outstanding! Big serving and comes with LARGE homemade roll. The next day I tried one of the daily specials, I think it was called Caribeann Chicken bowl. It was also OUTSTANDING! Very flavorful with fresh cilantro....
Too delicious!
Great food...Friendly people...I'll definitely be back!
Very unique menu with a great variety of food. Delicious soup! Have to go back and try the handmade ice cream.
Awesome Crew and Very Very Delicious Food
Impressive

We happened upon thIs cute place while sightseeing. Hubs had a pulled pork sandwich, I had a Bohemian sandwich and kids had turkey. We all said these were some of best we’ve ever had. Wish we were closer because we’d be back. Staff was very friendly and it had a relaxed vibe. Yummy!
Very friendly and good
Very friendly
Amazing place, hours should be longer and the place really needs a better way of taking peoples orders, having every wait in the entry way and only taking a few orders at a time is not working well
Food is fantastic, but it does got over crowded during lunch
I absolutely loved the place. Good vibes, good atmosphere, friendly staff, and great food! One of the best little places in the city. A local jewel truly!

Omg! I looooove this place their mac n cheese and mashies are 100 they are a must. The sandwiches are soooooo filling and flavorful. If you are ever near Springfield this place is worth a try. I'm a very picky eater... and they have won me over.

Such a great place! Had the Cuban (could only eat half) and it was perfectly spicy delicious. That peanut butter chocolate bar is awesome as well. The whole place is like walking into your best friend's kitchen for a casual get-together. Wish I was in town longer.
This is best restuarant around, it's not even close. If you're in Springfield for one day, make sure this is your meal. You won't be disappointed.
Great food. Cool atmosphere. Friendly staff.
The Cubano sandwich is Ecellent!
Food is amazing really pricey but worth it

Good food, but it took a long time to get it. There's no where near enough seating for people in there and I don't know why but a worker kept being friendly to everyone but acted weird towards my group.
Love their home made food.

The service was great! The food was great! Huge sandwiches! I had to take half home and that rarely happens. I thought I would have a hard time finding a place to sit because the seating area is long and narrow but found a spot on a barstool with ease. A group of 4 or more might have a slightly more difficult time if it's busy. I will definitely go back next time I'm in town!
Really good food but be ready for a wait if they are busy.
Fantastic food!
Great food. Need to do togo at all times. Lost my service.
Looking for a nice place to enjoy a great lunch in downtown Springfield? You gotta give this place a try!! You won't be disappointed.
Quaint little place with killer food❤
So glad we got to try this newer lunch spot in downtown Springfield.  The Cubano was fabulous.
Excellent food and great selection. Served fast. Highly recommend this place.

Unique flavorful dishes with a home cooked vibe. The place is small and quaint, but makes seating difficult at times. Don't be scared off by a line at the door. They do a pretty good job of managing the inflow given the size and popularity. It is worth the wait!
Excellent sandwiches.  Totally a 5.
Good food but busy and a little expensive
The food is homemade hot and fresh,my new #1 Spot!
Great place. Fun environment!

Stopped in for lunche on a Friday and there was a line out the door.  We ordered and were lucky enough to get a seat.  The staff was kind and the food was amazing.  Order the mac and cheese - you won't be dissappointed.  The food reminds me of some of Chicago's best sandwhich joints.

Such a little gem. The food is amazing. Everything I have tried is incredibly delicious. Sometimes you have search if you want a lighter meal, but the Long Nine Salad is great for a lighter option, and you can add their chicken which I would highly recommend. For hearty fare, they have plenty of great options and all are very tasty. Great flavors all around. Sidenote: try the cajun dirty rice and get their early before it sells out for the day!
Excellent food and service.
The Roast Beef was excellent!! Great place for lunch in downtown Springfield
Kind of hipsterish but food good.
Great sandwiches, but a very small place that fills up quickly.
The food was Great!  The staff were very friendly.  I will definitely go back.

It's one of a few places to eat an early dinner  (like, 4:30) on a Friday evening. Menu is on the wall, order at the counter. I didn't know what to expect food quality wise with a small-scale place, but you should try it. The food was very good. I would go back if I end up in town again.

Long Nine Junction is hands down one of the best restaurants in downtown Springfield. There's not much down here for food and this diamond in the rough really stands out. The Apple Butter Pork n' Mac was absolutely delicious. The portions are a perfect size for a nice enjoyable meal and the price is spot on. Even the staff is friendly and pleasant to talk to. Everyone in our group enjoyed their meal and will be back. Give them a try, you won't be disappointed!
I had the 1/2 chicken special, and it was incredible! Delicious food, great service!
Outstanding Cuban sandwich!  Great atmosphere and fantastic employees!  Looking forward to returning and trying much more of the menu in the near future!  Best gooey butter cake I have had in years!

Food was excellent. I had a sandwich, but the Pot Roast looked delicious. Staff was laid back and helpful. Right across the street from the Old State Capitol, and not a bad walk from the Capitol Complex. Good vibe for a laid back lunch. I'll be eating here again. And again.

We loved our meal at Long Nine Junction.  Really good food, good portion size.  Great setting across from the original Illinois capital downtown Springfield.  Very friendly workers and really great service.  Not a lot of seating room inside.  Would definitely go back.
Excellent Pork Thai bowl! Turned out to be a wonderful surprise. Every member of our group thoroughly enjoyed their meals including the Cuban and French dip.
Sandwiches are killer. Everything house made.
Long Nine Junction has some of the best food in Springfield. I've yet to have a meal that was not delicious!
Some of dishes are quite salty, but the rest is perfect
Great food!
Great food!! Great service :)
Friendly staff. Great atmosphere.
Little pricey but good food. $10+ for a lunch seems steep.
Excellent food.  Had the steakmelt sandwich amazing... Mac n Cheese  amazing...
This place is awesome. Best restaurant in Springfield.
Great experience. The food was delicious. View fantastic. And atmosphere chill. Cory and Emily have made a great thing in downtown Springfield, Illinois.

One of the very best spots in town. Everything is excellent. Prepared in house. Generous portions and very reasonable prices. If you're trying to decide between Long Nine and another spot, choose Long Nine. You won't be disappointed.
Top notch!!! Great and friendly customer service! Steakhouse melt for the W! Best Mac n cheese!!

This was the BEST turkey bacon ranch wrap I have ever had!! The place is clean and might I say ADORABLE!! The staff are super friendly and helpful. My boyfriend had the bbq chicken and Mac, he said it was the best Mac and cheese he’s had! A little pricey but completely worth it!

Excellent sandwiches!!! Fresh ingredients. Food is hot when it hits the table, and, well... you just need to see for yourself. We’re headed there tomorrow for the 3rd time...  Good physical location, but their food deserves a better venue...
Good food which draws in customers but crowded because of space. I can overlook the crowd for the food!!
Great food.  No beer, though
So good! I always get the apple butter pork n mac bowl....DELISH!!!!
Very good food, great location

This place has courteous staff and awesome food. They're sandwiches we delicious and reasonably priced for being in a downtown location. I recommend trying the "Tijuana"!  Try to beat the lunch crowd though, because the wait can get long. The wait is definitely worth it for the food though!
First-time guest, and I LOVED this place! The food was absolutely delicious, and the staff- wonderful! It such an adorably quaint place. I would definitely come back!!
Totally surprised by this place. We came by when our first choice was closed. Best sandwiches we’ve had in Springfield!!!

Oh my goodness!  Glad I found this diamond in the rough.  From the first bite to my last this roast beef is to die for.  Ciabatta roll yum and so fresh.  Even the fresh lettuce salad was good.  Best food I've had in a very long time.  Do yourself a favor and eat here.
A hidden gem in downtown Springfield
Amazing quality and consistently awesome execution.
The Parisian might be the best sandwich I've ever had in Springfield. Owners are great and take pride in their business!
Love the food, amazing mac and cheese. The go to on trend lunch place in downtown Springfield.

I took my daughter Julia to lunch at Long Nine, at her suggestion. I always yield to her recommendations - this visit underlined my confidence in her opinions. I ordered the French Dip sandwich, which happened to be THE VERY BEST I EVER TASTED! I couldn't get over it. Indescribable! Julia ordered their super-deluxe grilled cheese sandwich. If you are tired of dropping your bucks for boring so-so, fare, you really need to go Downtown and visit this place!

Great local spot downtown. Food was delicious, staff was very friendly. Unique concept for a restaurant. The menu changes frequently, so don't expect the same thing every visit. Good for a quick lunch or a casual date night.

First time in and the food was amazing! I had the brisket sandwich special on home made focacia bread. So good! The side of jus put it over the top. Can't wait to come back and try more. Not to be missed!
Amazing!
Great local lunch and dinner restaurant rooted in local history. Delicious food
Amazing Food and Friendly Staff! You’ve to pass by when in Springfield
Good sandwich, had a Cubanno.
Good food, a little different but very good.
Great local lunch place. The grilled cheese is fantastic.
Excellent sandwiches! Great service! And it was really quick.
The food is delicious, haven’t had a bad meal yet. Hope that they can expand so they have more seating, other than that, it’s cute, chic place to eat.
Delicious local cuisine food for an affordable price. Great customer service. Casual setting.
Good food and service.
Food was good. Prices are a bit steep though. Hard to justify $10 for just a sandwich and a bag of chips...

Had a really great experience at this hidden gem.  This was a unique experience in comparison to your traditional restaurant. The environment is very hipster or modern,  its tough to describe, you will have to check it our for yourself.  Emily greeted us when we walked in and gave us a very detailed breakdown of the menu and everything they offer.  It's actually a pretty good sized menu considering it is a small diner.  I had the roast beef and french dip which was amazing.  When we finished, Emily surprised us with some very fluffy cookies!

Located right across the street from the Old Capitol building and Capitol Plaza, Long Nine Junction is another find in a series of tasty sandwich and soup shops located in the area.  Their Menu is not extensive and it does not need to be. The staff is super friendly and although seating space is limited, the food is fantastic and another testament to downtown Springfield’s amazing lunch fare options.  I had the Cubano sandwich with chips and their bottled soda – delicious. Definitely, worth a stop by, but only for lunch as they are only open from 11am-3pm.

Farm to table restaurant opened by a local chef.  Food is amazing.  They always have a daily special which is highly recommended.  All produce and meat is locally sourced.  Breads are made in house.  Nothing frozen or fried.  Delicious!!!!
Great eclectic food choices, great welcoming staff and terrific atmosphere. Our favorite restaurant in Springfield. Cheers!

This is a wonderful restaurant. Visited twice on a recent trip. Exceptional roast chicken and sides. Everything tasty and well prepared. Very busy at lunchtime. Dinner is much quieter.  Very unique restaurant.
Does not disappoint. Menu may be intimidating but everything is delicious! Even their salads. Highly recommend!

I have eaten here multiple times for lunch and dinner over the last several months and have yet to have a bad meal. The French Dip is a solid standby and the Cubano is a personal favorite. The owners are very involved in day to day operation and always come around to check on their customers while they eat as well as clear tables. Usually quite busy during lunch, I recommend planning a little extra time if you eat there during the day.

Great place for lunch, while visiting historical Abraham Lincoln attractions, in downtown Springfield, IL. On the small side but very cute/retro. The menu is on the wall, when you walk in: appetizers, sandwiches, soups, & entrees. You order, at counter, then your meal is brought to your table. We ordered the mixed cheese grilled cheese sandwich (soooo yummy!!!), on homemade garlic bread. All sandwich platters come with bagged chips but, for $3, you can change them out for a specialty side, which is what we did. My husband got their mac & cheese side and liked it. I got the cilantro rice. It was good but I was sorry I got it because the sandwiches are pretty darn big and I was full after eating mine! All of their bread is homemade and I noticed several people had soup with one of the giant rolls and it looked fantastic! If I was to go back, that’s what I’d order, although I’d miss that grilled cheese. On second thought, my hubby & I could both get the soup & roll, then split the grilled cheese! For drinks, they’ve got some old fashioned bottled sodas, as well as tea, lemon water, etc. We also got their homemade peanut butter cookies. I’ll just say you’ve GOT to have them! A pleasant & pleasing place to eat!!!
Long nine junction was great the food was good
The food is amazing, the atmosphere is very comfortable, the staff is more than friendly. Absolutely a must-go visit when you come to Springfield!
Great sandwiches.
Fantastic food, chill atmosphere. Great for lunch or early dinner.

Impressed , very Impressed! This food was so flavorful and tender that it's almost beyond belief. (No I don't have any connection to this place). It's a walked in first come first serve, then your seated. This is not a large dinning area. After my experience eating here I would have zero issues with waiting for an open table. I can tell you I have every reason to return.amd try every item on their menu. Food was absoutley outstanding.  Staff encounter was perfect. Check them out!

Excellent food!  The Apple butter BBQ pulled pork and homemade mac and cheese were outstanding!  Great coffee - warm and friendly service - cozy atmosphere.  We will definitely be back the next time we visit Springfield.
This is the 8th time I've been here and it gets better every single time! The food, as well as the service is incredible! I would recommend this place to anyone!!
Extremely quick and courteous service!  It was unbelievably tasty and the staff was extremely helpful and welcoming! Also a great atmosphere :)
Food is absolutely fantastic. Highly recommended.
Awesome food.  Original and creative.
Will be back here, great food, great service.
First time visiting, hardy food with flavor.
Excellent food!
Great food and cool eclectic atmosphere!
Very nice, good and tasty food.
The best new restaurant to open in Springfield in a long time. The food is always amazing and it's a great atmosphere. If you haven't tried it, do yourself a favor and try this for lunch or dinner.
Food is so tasty 😊👍
Best half roasted chicken with herloim tomatoes, fresh green and mozarella cheese.  A limited menu, but the food and atmosphere is excellent.  Stop by next time you are in town 👍
Excellent taste, presentation, and very friendly owner and helpers.  They run a limited menu but what they had was excellent.

If you reading this review wondering where to eat go here - this is 5* restaurant quality food at prices of Panera bread. The food is great not by accident - somebody who works there (may be the owner) said they shop for ingredients at Farmers market, so things like tomatoes are way more tasty. I would rate this restaurant as one of the best eats in state. This will be my go to place whenever I am in the area.
Fantastic fresh food, fun atmosphere,  friendly service!
Cool, kind of eclectic place.

We came to Springfield Illinois to see President Lincoln's house and found this awesome culinary experience.  You won't be dissapointed.  The staff is fantastic and the food was jaw dropping delicious.  Totally worth the drive.   We will be back from Houston Texas.

Phenomenal food,service with a smile, very genuinely friendly owners. They have set lunches on their menu, in addition they create other meals almost on a daily basis . Try them all they're yummy.. .  The quality of food you receive when you do a takeout  order is exactly  the same. as when you eat in the restaurant , Juts a great restaurant They will be around for a long time.
Had the BLT salad. SO delicious. Served on top of their homemade focaccia bread. Self serve water and utensils. Cute relaxed setting.
Incredible tasting. Nice atmosphere. Love the help yourself drink station
Had the slow roast beef; best we've ever had! ALL food fantastic! Friendly & hospitable staff! FUN place, too! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Great food and atmosphere. Great for night and weekends. Maybe not a good lunch place when you're on the clock, it takes a little bit of time to get your food. Well worth the wait if you've got the time.
Awesome - Motions - slow roast beef meal for lunch! I'll be back for other to try.
Great food, great staff.. ..
The food was delicious! The atmosphere was nice. Would definitely recommend this to anyone.
Very cute place. Wouldn't recommend the salads, but everything else, including service, was excellent.
Everything is superb
Great food, friendly atmosphere. I highly recommend the French dip sandwich!
Good food, awesome service. Had the French dip with Mac& cheese... I am convinced that the chef has made a deal with a devil at a crossroads to get that much flavor in to the food!
Everything. Atmosphere, food, setting all great.
Excellent food and nice small place caring attention. Cubano sandwich was awesome and homemade soup!
Great food and atmosphere
Amazing food French dip is my favorite!!!

Stoped here on our drive from Chicago to St. Louis. I have been dreaming about it ever since The food was amazing! Roast beef special, homemade bread, salads, all so good. And I loved the bottled pops and lemonade and ice tea station. The set up and decor are perfect and the owner could not have been friendlier.
Amazing what you can with simple ingredients. Awesome experience.
Awesome food and fantastic service.
Great food and atmosphere.
Friendly people with excellent food.
This place was amazing. Very cool vibe/decor. Food was amazing and employee's were incredibly helpful.
Private dinner tonight- superb food and really friendly service. Very nice!

Really enjoyed the food, but not the prices. Down home style with fine dining flavors. Great for a quick, casual lunch date or treating yourself to a good takeout meal. Family dinner cost a pretty penny.
An incredibly tasty and enjoyable experience. The food and drink options are all great and the service is remarkable- I will be spending a lot of time here.

Tried it last week for dinner, our first visit. Walked past twice before finding the entrance. Glad we took the trouble: the posole verde and the kha were excellent, as was the large cookie. Nice atmosphere - friendly and very welcoming. This is definitely on our list of local restaurants to return to for a terrific, reasonable priced meal.
Amazing food, great atmosphere, family friendly, amazing place

Atmosphere is great.  Staff really friendly.  Food is great, not simply a brand and potato place.  Food is different.  Chef has many years of experience in one of the top restaurants in Springfield.  I sure want to return there.

When Chef Corey left Augie's Front Burner, I was extremely disappointed, as he's one of the most talented chefs I've encountered. However, his prowess is not wasted on the least at his new venture, Long Nine Junction. I got to try 2 sandwiches. The Parisian was arguably the best sandwich I've had in years, and I'd put his Cubano up against any Cuban sandwich I've had. I'm genuinely impressed and can't wait for my next visit!
The owners were really nice,the place was very clean and the food was amazing. Great addition to Downtown Springfield. Awesome  place for a work session with your laptop too 😁
Just stumbled across this gem, fantastic place to grab a bite to eat, would highly recommend! 6 Stars ✨
